# t/mail/follow-up-no-stale-reply.test — a turn sends ONLY what THAT turn produced.
# out/ is emptied at the start of every turn (decision-019), so a prior turn's
# reply.txt (or an attachment) cannot linger and be re-sent when the agent writes
# nothing new — the "same email twice" bug (task 3827: the agent resumed, decided
# the task was already done, wrote no reply, and käsi re-mailed the old one).
#
# This is also a twin-fidelity guard. The sim harness now reports the WHOLE out/
# box as its manifest, exactly as the on-disk harness walks the out/ directory, so
# a stale re-send is visible to the gate. Reporting only the current turn's writes
# (the old sim behaviour) is what hid this bug from the ring.

send allow-sender   { address owner@example.test }
send set-reply-from { address kasi@decode.ee }

# Turn 1: the agent answers, with a body AND an attachment.
deliver { from owner@example.test; to kasi@decode.ee; subject "research"; body "look into X" }
agent { out reply.txt "First answer."; out notes.csv "a,b,c" }
task 1 status is awaiting-user
outbound count is 1
outbound last body matches "*First answer*"
outbound last attachments is notes.csv

# Turn 2: the user follows up, but the agent writes NOTHING this turn — exactly the
# reported incident, where a resumed run concluded "task complete, stopping". Because
# out/ was emptied at the turn's start, there is no reply.txt to harvest, so NOTHING
# is sent. Before decision-019 the stale turn-1 reply.txt was re-sent here.
deliver { from owner@example.test; reply-to-last; body "actually, also cover Y" }
agent { exit 0 }
task 1 status is awaiting-user
outbound count is 1

# Turn 3: the agent does the work and writes a FRESH reply — with no attachment this
# time. The turn-1 notes.csv must NOT ride along, because out/ was reset.
deliver { from owner@example.test; reply-to-last; body "now send it" }
agent { out reply.txt "Second answer, now covering Y." }
task 1 status is awaiting-user
outbound count is 2
outbound last body matches "*covering Y*"
outbound last attachments is ""
